WEBVTT

00:02.536 --> 00:04.838
Sorry, Dad.
You wanted to have a talk?

00:04.938 --> 00:06.006
I did.

00:06.107 --> 00:09.243
Uh, I-I've put it off
long enough. It's time.

00:09.343 --> 00:11.079
Uh, uh, uh,
you seem to be

00:11.179 --> 00:13.047
getting closer
with your girlfriend,

00:13.147 --> 00:14.615
and when that is so,

00:14.715 --> 00:17.551
certain
bodily...initiatives

00:17.651 --> 00:20.088
are engaged...uh,

00:20.188 --> 00:24.024
and, uh, uh,
you may find yourself

00:24.125 --> 00:26.727
wanting to have...

00:26.827 --> 00:29.563
Italian ice!
Sound good?

00:30.564 --> 00:32.366
Okay, Ray.

00:32.466 --> 00:33.601
Look.

00:33.701 --> 00:35.803
Everyone...

00:35.903 --> 00:37.905
ripens at their own pace.

00:38.005 --> 00:40.108
I mean, when I was your age,
I certainly wasn't --

00:40.208 --> 00:42.576
Ah, maybe I could have.
I don't know. It's hard to say.

00:42.676 --> 00:44.978
Actually, there was this
one party where this chick

00:45.079 --> 00:47.915
Lana DeLagala
was giving me these vibes.

00:48.015 --> 00:50.318
I had just gotten
this suede jacket.

00:50.418 --> 00:51.952
It was really cool.
I smelled like a book.

00:52.052 --> 00:53.254
You know what?
That -- Forget that.

00:53.354 --> 00:55.423
Back to our talk.

00:55.523 --> 00:56.924
Ooh!
[ Tires screech ]

00:57.024 --> 00:58.792
A baby panda
at the zoo?!

01:00.728 --> 01:02.563
We should give
this guy a ride.

01:02.663 --> 01:05.466
**

01:05.566 --> 01:07.135
Man: This is me.

01:07.235 --> 01:08.636
[ Brakes squeal ]

01:08.736 --> 01:09.770
[ Belt unbuckles ]
Thanks for the lift.

01:09.870 --> 01:11.505
You sure
you have to go?

01:11.605 --> 01:12.906
[ Door closes ]
[ Sighs ]

01:13.006 --> 01:15.943
Screw it.
Ray, we're having the talk.

01:16.043 --> 01:17.178
All right.

01:17.278 --> 01:18.946
And I want you to know

01:19.046 --> 01:21.182
that if you have any other
questions, you can come to me.

01:21.282 --> 01:23.684
Dad. Wow.

01:23.784 --> 01:25.853
Taylor and I
are so far from that.

01:25.953 --> 01:28.889
But the fact that you thought
I needed the talk

01:28.922 --> 01:31.592
is a huge, huge honor.

01:31.692 --> 01:33.661
I have a lot
of follow-up questions.

01:33.761 --> 01:35.329
Sure. You can ask them
on the way back.

01:35.429 --> 01:37.131
What's Spanish
for "U-turn?"

01:41.169 --> 01:45.173
Hey. Look at you.
Up for parole already.

01:45.273 --> 01:48.209
I found a bunch of scrubs
on the school payroll

01:48.309 --> 01:49.643
who can act as aides
to the new

01:49.743 --> 01:51.379
special-needs students
starting this week.

01:51.479 --> 01:53.046
And today, Kenneth and I
are going to train them.

01:53.147 --> 01:55.048
Oh. Dr. Miller
wanted you to do that?

01:55.149 --> 01:55.949
We'll find out.

01:55.983 --> 01:57.351
Ahh.

01:57.451 --> 01:59.620
Father,
this is for you.

02:01.722 --> 02:03.524
Is this a pen? Why?

02:03.624 --> 02:04.725
I am a man now.

02:04.825 --> 02:06.527
You made that very clear
yesterday.

02:06.627 --> 02:09.997
So I wanted to give you a token
from one man to another.

02:10.097 --> 02:15.703
**

02:15.803 --> 02:17.871
Why does Ray think
he's a man now?

02:17.971 --> 02:19.973
Ah, prepare
to be impressed.

02:20.073 --> 02:23.377
I took some initiative and
I gave Ray "the talk" yesterday.

02:23.477 --> 02:25.145
I wasn't sure how
I'd be at it at first,

02:25.246 --> 02:26.880
but once I got going,
it really...

02:26.980 --> 02:29.317
clicked -- clicked.
Ah, it's a twister.

02:29.417 --> 02:31.018
So that was the first time
you did that, was it?

02:31.118 --> 02:34.555
Meaning, you gave Ray the talk
before his older brother.

02:34.655 --> 02:38.091
Don't we always say, whatever
the other kids get, JJ gets?

02:38.192 --> 02:41.362
Yes, but Ray's got
a girlfriend right now.

02:41.462 --> 02:44.765
You know, it felt like the time
for a father-son moment.

02:44.865 --> 02:46.700
But JJ deserves
father-son moments.

02:46.800 --> 02:48.236
Just 'cause we're living
in an upside-down world

02:48.336 --> 02:50.103
where Ray has a girlfriend
doesn't change that.

02:50.204 --> 02:51.605
Of course it doesn't.

02:51.705 --> 02:53.707
And I know exactly
how to fix this.

02:53.807 --> 02:57.911
And until you do...
pen goes in the hair.

02:58.011 --> 02:59.213
Aw!

02:59.313 --> 03:03.351
[ School bell rings,
indistinct conversations ]

03:04.184 --> 03:06.053
O-Okay.
What's this, weirdo?

03:06.153 --> 03:09.423
That Brandon kid up there?
He's so jealous of me.

03:09.523 --> 03:11.259
You?
What's he jealous of?

03:11.359 --> 03:13.627
The whole package,
I assume.

03:13.727 --> 03:15.296
Just wish his jealousy
didn't make him

03:15.396 --> 03:17.398
pull elaborate mind games
to torture me.

03:17.498 --> 03:20.468
Ohh. [ Scoffs ]
He's picking on you.

03:20.568 --> 03:22.135
Okay, you just believed Mom
when she told you

03:22.236 --> 03:24.605
everyone who picks on you
is jealous.

03:24.705 --> 03:26.374
Look. I'll take care
of this kid.

03:26.474 --> 03:29.076
[ Loudly ] No! I don't need your
help! You're my little sister!

03:29.176 --> 03:30.978
[ Whispering ]
Thank you.

03:31.078 --> 03:34.415
**

03:34.515 --> 03:37.451
Aah! Bats! Bats!

03:37.551 --> 03:38.952
Brandon,
I'm Ray's little --

03:39.052 --> 03:41.422
Ray, buddy,
don't open your backpack.

03:41.522 --> 03:42.756
You don't tell me
what to do.

03:42.856 --> 03:44.124
[ Gasps ]

03:44.224 --> 03:45.459
Aah! More bats!

03:45.559 --> 03:47.795
-[ Laughs ]
-How'd you even do that?

03:47.895 --> 03:49.830
I thought I knew a thing or two
about messing with Ray,

03:49.930 --> 03:52.132
but this is next-level.
Thanks.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.568
Plus I fed the pigeons a ton
of corn so they'd make a mess,

03:54.668 --> 03:56.003
which is great since Ray...

03:56.103 --> 03:57.505
Both:
Hates bird poop!

03:59.340 --> 04:01.108
-I'm Dylan.
-Brandon.

04:01.208 --> 04:04.011
Great. Now you're
jealous of me together.

04:04.111 --> 04:06.847
Good morning.
Thank you all for being here.

04:06.947 --> 04:08.616
My name is Maya DiMeo,

04:08.716 --> 04:10.984
and you know
your old colleague Kenneth.

04:11.084 --> 04:13.654
Maya, can I move away
from this board?

04:13.754 --> 04:16.324
You may erase the arrow
pointing at you.

04:16.424 --> 04:19.660
So we'll be preparing to work
with some wonderful children

04:19.760 --> 04:21.929
with a variety
of different needs.

04:22.029 --> 04:24.998
One is visually impaired,
one has cerebral palsy.

04:25.098 --> 04:27.468
Woot! Woot!
C.P. in the house!

04:27.568 --> 04:29.970
One has autism.
[ Sighs ]

04:30.070 --> 04:32.340
One has nine heads.

04:32.440 --> 04:36.009
One was the original drummer
in The Beatles.

04:37.978 --> 04:39.547
Give me that.

04:39.647 --> 04:41.649
[ Gasps ]
This is dirty.

04:41.749 --> 04:43.851
As a rough guide,
I've provided copies

04:43.951 --> 04:46.887
of my own son's care manual,
which I trust you've read.

04:46.987 --> 04:49.056
Any questions? Yes.

04:49.156 --> 04:53.226
If this is a new job,
do we get all new vacation days?

04:53.327 --> 04:55.396
Oh, you got big plans,
White Shaq?

04:55.496 --> 04:57.531
George and Amal expecting you
in Lake Como?

04:57.631 --> 04:59.633
I don't have an answer
for that, sir.

04:59.733 --> 05:00.834
Yes?

05:00.934 --> 05:02.636
Them kids.
Is they contagious?

05:02.736 --> 05:06.206
No, they is not contagious!
How did you ever teach English?!

05:06.306 --> 05:09.176
I am offering you
a chance to matter,

05:09.276 --> 05:12.045
instead of half-assing your way
through your whole lives.

05:12.145 --> 05:14.314
Is any of you int--
Ugh!

05:14.415 --> 05:17.084
Are any of you
interested at all?

05:19.853 --> 05:21.422
They are useless!

05:21.522 --> 05:24.592
Why can't you fire them
and hire qualified aides?

05:24.692 --> 05:25.826
Different reasons.

05:25.926 --> 05:28.028
Uh, the librarian
is tenured,

05:28.128 --> 05:29.397
the crossing guard
is a descendant

05:29.497 --> 05:31.399
of the Lafayette
the school is named for...

05:31.499 --> 05:33.901
The woman who picked
her nose and flung it at
Kenneth is a Lafayette?

05:34.001 --> 05:35.436
A lot of inbreeding
in that family.

05:35.536 --> 05:37.104
Well, they all have to go.

05:37.204 --> 05:39.907
Yeah. I'm not leaving this room
until you fire them.

05:40.007 --> 05:42.843
Then I will leave this room
and hide from you.

05:44.378 --> 05:46.079
Wait.
What if they quit?

05:46.179 --> 05:48.115
Hmm. If they quit...

05:48.215 --> 05:50.017
that means that you don't
have to fire them,

05:50.117 --> 05:51.785
which means we can
replace them, yes?

05:51.885 --> 05:54.187
I suppose that's true.
Well, then,
I'll make them quit.

05:55.589 --> 05:57.357
[ Door slams ]
And stay out.

05:57.458 --> 05:59.226
Nice little
surprise, right?

05:59.326 --> 06:00.794
Here we are.

06:00.894 --> 06:03.296
Huh? Father, son,
and Mother...

06:03.397 --> 06:04.965
Nature.

06:05.065 --> 06:08.636
You know, as long as we're here,
it just occurred to me.

06:08.736 --> 06:11.772
How would you like
to have...the talk?

06:13.040 --> 06:16.710
[ Beep, ethereal music plays ]
Ahh.

06:16.810 --> 06:19.647
The human body is a
miraculous thing...
[ Laughs ]

06:19.747 --> 06:22.616
...capable
of incredible...

06:22.716 --> 06:26.086
"You don't have to do this.

06:26.186 --> 06:29.757
I know about S-E-X."

06:29.857 --> 06:31.224
[ Music stops ]

06:31.324 --> 06:32.960
You win again, Internet.

06:33.060 --> 06:37.465
But just let me know if you ever
want to talk about anything.

06:37.565 --> 06:40.568
All right? I'm your dad.
That's what I'm here for.

06:40.668 --> 06:42.503
"There is something."

06:42.603 --> 06:44.137
Bring it on.

06:44.237 --> 06:46.507
"Will I get to...

06:46.607 --> 06:49.677
have a W-I-- wife?

06:49.777 --> 06:51.512
Be a dad?"

06:51.612 --> 06:56.684
Uh. "Take care
of a F-A-- family?"

06:59.587 --> 07:01.822
Yeah. 'Course!

07:01.922 --> 07:03.323
Yeah, you can do anything
you set your mind to.

07:03.423 --> 07:06.259
My answer to that is a --
is a good old...

07:06.359 --> 07:08.161
[ a la The Three Stooges ]
Soitenly!

07:15.335 --> 07:17.871
It is 2:17. I told you to be
here at 2:00 p.m. sharp!

07:17.971 --> 07:19.873
We were all here
waiting for you.

07:19.973 --> 07:22.042
What'd you call me?
You call me a "ewe?"

07:22.142 --> 07:25.012
That is a baby cow!
I think a baby cow
is a calf.

07:25.112 --> 07:27.047
Ah, well, lookee here.

07:27.147 --> 07:30.851
We got ourselves
a real baby-animal expert.

07:30.951 --> 07:33.020
I'm gonna call you
Petting Zoo.

07:33.887 --> 07:36.389
You make me sick! Can't believe
any of you want to be aides.

07:36.490 --> 07:37.891
We don't want
to be aides.

07:37.991 --> 07:40.393
We do want to keep
getting our checks.

07:40.494 --> 07:41.695
Pick it up!

07:41.795 --> 07:43.831
In fact, all of you
on the ground.

07:43.931 --> 07:46.634
And while you're down there,
give me 20 jumping jacks.

07:46.734 --> 07:48.536
On the ground?
I think you mean push-ups.

07:48.636 --> 07:52.873
Ohh. We got ourselves
a real exercise expert.

07:52.973 --> 07:55.175
I'm gonna call you
Jack LaLanne.

07:55.275 --> 07:56.977
But I'm Petting Zoo.

07:57.077 --> 07:59.747
Maya. [ Chuckles ]

07:59.847 --> 08:01.549
What does this have to do
with being an aide?

08:01.649 --> 08:03.584
Oh, no, no, no. Nothing. I want
to get these losers to quit

08:03.684 --> 08:05.753
so we can hire a bunch
of competent people
to replace them.

08:05.853 --> 08:07.354
Well, you didn't even
give them a chance!

08:07.454 --> 08:08.722
They can't take care
of these kids.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.558
You got to be special
to do this job, Kenneth.

08:10.658 --> 08:12.893
Well, you didn't think
I was very special
when I first showed up.

08:12.993 --> 08:15.829
Seeing as how far we've come,
haven't you learned anything?

08:15.929 --> 08:17.264
No.

08:17.364 --> 08:20.100
If this is the game you're
playing, you can play it alone.

08:20.200 --> 08:23.537
Well, hoo-wee!
One loser gone already!

08:26.406 --> 08:27.908
Aah!
[ Screams ]

08:28.008 --> 08:29.109
Aah!

08:31.745 --> 08:33.581
Wow. You were right.

08:33.681 --> 08:35.749
Duct tape is just
as fun as birds.

08:35.849 --> 08:37.017
What is going on?!

08:37.117 --> 08:38.385
Hon, will you
give us a minute?

08:39.687 --> 08:41.689
You brought him
into our house?!

08:41.789 --> 08:43.591
Yeah!
Nowhere's safe now.

08:43.691 --> 08:45.258
We've had our fun,
you and I,

08:45.358 --> 08:47.761
but Brandon just takes it
to a different level.

08:47.861 --> 08:50.097
Did you at least figure out
what his problem with me is?

08:50.197 --> 08:51.264
He hates band kids.

08:51.364 --> 08:52.365
I'm not in band!

08:52.465 --> 08:54.301
I know.
Isn't he irrational?

08:54.401 --> 08:56.236
I think I might love him.

08:56.336 --> 08:57.571
What?!

08:57.671 --> 09:00.974
Oh, look at that.
Perfect.

09:01.074 --> 09:05.245
This is gonna make
a perfect s'more, right?

09:05.345 --> 09:09.249
S-O-I-T-- "Soitenly."

09:09.349 --> 09:11.318
Hey, we should go
for a walk

09:11.418 --> 09:13.120
and get some more
marshmallow sticks.

09:13.220 --> 09:16.289
"Let me do it."

09:16.389 --> 09:18.892
Uh, you want to go out alone,
you think?

09:18.992 --> 09:21.895
I mean, you could get lost
or -- or stuck...

09:21.995 --> 09:25.966
"You said
I could do anything.

09:26.066 --> 09:31.805
If I can have a family,
I can get some sticks."

09:31.905 --> 09:34.341
You know what?
You're right.

09:34.441 --> 09:37.144
You go get some sticks.
And I -- Okay.

09:37.244 --> 09:40.280
I will sit here
and not worry about

09:40.380 --> 09:43.116
where you are
or how you are...

09:43.216 --> 09:45.585
or bears.

09:47.955 --> 09:50.958
Okay, worms,
your first task today --

09:51.058 --> 09:54.594
take this hat and put it
in that window up there.

09:54.695 --> 09:58.198
Is this to show us that
the kids overcome challenges,

09:58.298 --> 10:00.000
so we need
to overcome things

10:00.100 --> 10:02.169
that seem impossible?
Sure.

10:02.269 --> 10:04.204
So, you want us to, like,
climb on top of each other?

10:04.304 --> 10:05.706
Somebody's gonna
get killed.

10:05.806 --> 10:07.540
Oh, are you out?
You're quitting?
No.

10:07.641 --> 10:10.010
Do it now, 'cause the other
things aren't any easier.

10:10.110 --> 10:12.212
So we're gonna make
a human ladder.

10:12.312 --> 10:14.381
Which one of you
is gonna be the base?

10:14.481 --> 10:17.317
What's the point of us
doing your housekeeping?

10:17.417 --> 10:18.786
Oh, well, if you want
it all to stop,

10:18.886 --> 10:20.821
you know the magic words --
"I Quit."

10:21.655 --> 10:24.357
What's the matter? Never
folded a fitted sheet before?

10:24.457 --> 10:26.326
[ Weakly ] It's hard
because of the elastic.

10:26.426 --> 10:28.696
Life's hard because
of the elastic!

10:28.796 --> 10:31.364
Right. Did you all bring your
toothbrushes like I instructed?

10:32.866 --> 10:34.567
Switch with your neighbor.

10:36.036 --> 10:37.237
And start brushing.

10:39.039 --> 10:41.041
Eww! Stop it!
You were just gonna do it?!

10:41.141 --> 10:42.375
What's the matter
with you people?!

10:42.475 --> 10:43.543
Why aren't you quitting?

10:43.643 --> 10:44.878
'Cause it's gonna
be worth it.

10:44.978 --> 10:46.479
What?
Who told you that?

10:46.579 --> 10:48.982
Kenneth. He told us
not to give up.

10:49.082 --> 10:51.084
You are kidding me.

10:51.184 --> 10:53.086
He also asked
we ain't tell her that.

10:53.186 --> 10:56.089
Congratulations.
You won this round. Go home.

10:56.189 --> 10:58.191
Ooh! You know
what could be fun?

10:58.291 --> 11:00.427
If we wrapped him up and put him
in a present at Christmas.

11:00.527 --> 11:02.930
You still think we'll be
bullying Ray at Christmas?

11:03.030 --> 11:04.097
[ Door opens ]

11:04.197 --> 11:05.265
I'm really happy.

11:05.365 --> 11:06.399
Me too.

11:09.536 --> 11:11.772
Kenneth, I assume
you know why I'm here.

11:11.872 --> 11:13.373
Well, I won't say
I'm not flattered.

11:13.473 --> 11:15.242
But I respect Jimmy
too much.

11:15.342 --> 11:16.676
Good night.

11:17.377 --> 11:18.712
You're ruining my plan.

11:18.812 --> 11:20.413
Why'd you tell those
losers not to quit?

11:20.513 --> 11:21.715
What'd you even
say to them anyway?

11:23.283 --> 11:24.584
That you're an enormous
pain in the ass and that
they shouldn't let you win.

11:24.684 --> 11:25.953
Excuse me!

11:26.053 --> 11:28.421
I am a joy in the ass!

11:28.521 --> 11:30.357
I need people
who care about the kids.

11:30.457 --> 11:33.426
Well, they might care. They're
sticking it out with you.

11:33.526 --> 11:35.428
No! They're just
doing the bare minimum

11:35.528 --> 11:36.964
to protect
their cushy jobs.

11:37.064 --> 11:38.431
What happens
when my back is turned?

11:38.531 --> 11:39.566
I don't even want to know.

11:39.666 --> 11:41.802
Stop sabotaging
me sabotaging them!

11:41.902 --> 11:43.303
You know what?
[ Chuckles ]

11:43.403 --> 11:45.572
On second thought, it's not
like Jimmy's my brother.

11:45.672 --> 11:47.107
Come on in.

11:48.141 --> 11:50.443
Jimmy:
Nice s'more sticks.

11:50.543 --> 11:52.980
Hmm. Too obvious.

11:53.080 --> 11:54.314
Enh.

11:54.414 --> 12:01.121
**

12:01.221 --> 12:02.923
Come on, buddy.
Right over here.

12:03.023 --> 12:07.995
**

12:08.095 --> 12:13.133
**

12:13.233 --> 12:15.735
Ca-caw!

12:15.836 --> 12:22.509
**

12:22.609 --> 12:24.477
Hey! JJ.

12:24.577 --> 12:26.746
I was just following
this beautiful bird.

12:26.847 --> 12:28.949
Did you hear it?
It sounded like "Ca-caw!"

12:29.049 --> 12:31.785
I'm sorry. I just
wanted you to be safe.

12:31.885 --> 12:33.153
There was that steep hill,

12:33.253 --> 12:35.288
and I know you get nervous
about flipping. I...

12:35.388 --> 12:41.494
"This is D- dumb.
Let's just go home."

12:42.762 --> 12:44.832
I am never
getting my pen back.

12:51.271 --> 12:53.140
We don't stop
until we get this.

12:53.240 --> 12:54.641
-Yeah!
-This is important.

12:54.741 --> 12:57.044
For the reason what
the England lady said.

12:57.144 --> 12:59.279
Bloody hell.
They do care.

12:59.379 --> 13:01.214
Looking good, guys!
We can do this!

13:01.314 --> 13:04.051
Yeah, let's keep talking, 'cause
you're getting so much lighter.

13:04.151 --> 13:07.054
Okay. Just hang for a sec.
We'll be on the road soon.

13:11.724 --> 13:13.393
Whoa! What was that?

13:13.493 --> 13:15.562
[ Pounding on door ]

13:15.662 --> 13:16.729
JJ! Are you out there?

13:16.830 --> 13:18.531
[ Beeping ]
Okay.

13:18.631 --> 13:21.534
Look. This is gonna be fine.
I, uh...

13:21.634 --> 13:23.736
Ohh...crap.
[ Phone beeps ]

13:23.837 --> 13:25.472
All right.
I don't have any service.

13:25.572 --> 13:27.875
Um, we'll just hang tight

13:27.975 --> 13:30.677
and wait for somebody
to come by and help, okay?

13:33.246 --> 13:34.714
J-- JJ?

13:34.814 --> 13:37.217
JJ?!

13:37.317 --> 13:39.019
JJ, stay put.
It's not safe.

13:39.119 --> 13:40.187
JJ!

13:40.287 --> 13:42.589
This is my worst sex talk ever.

13:47.360 --> 13:50.097
[ Animal howls in distance ]

13:53.266 --> 13:56.036
[ JJ breathing sharply ]

13:57.604 --> 13:58.939
[ Grunts ]

13:59.039 --> 14:01.774
I-I don't know how this works.

14:03.210 --> 14:06.179
[ Motor whines ]

14:06.279 --> 14:10.417
[ Motor whirs ]

14:10.517 --> 14:12.285
All right, Jimmy.
This is the big one.

14:12.385 --> 14:14.287
Y-a-a-ah! Ohh!

14:14.387 --> 14:16.456
That was not the big one.

14:16.556 --> 14:20.193
Look. I hate that you think
I'm a giant pain in the ass.

14:20.293 --> 14:22.529
But I was wrong
about those people.

14:22.629 --> 14:23.897
They do care.

14:23.997 --> 14:26.566
And I need your help
getting them ready.

14:26.666 --> 14:29.402
'Cause there's nobody better
to teach them.

14:29.502 --> 14:31.404
Well, okay.

14:31.504 --> 14:32.872
But on one condition.

14:32.973 --> 14:35.042
I'm the one that gets
to hold the whistle now.

14:35.142 --> 14:36.409
I didn't have a whistle.

14:36.509 --> 14:38.045
Okay, well, then,
I have no conditions.

14:38.145 --> 14:41.949
Now we're going to practice
chair-to-chair transfers.

14:42.049 --> 14:44.617
[ Theme from "Stripes" plays ]

14:47.220 --> 14:48.455
Kenneth: Aah!
[ Thud ]

14:48.555 --> 14:50.991
Did she say
chair-to-floor?!

14:51.091 --> 14:57.064
**

14:57.164 --> 14:59.566
[ Whistle blows ]

14:59.666 --> 15:02.402
**

15:02.502 --> 15:04.071
Now, another thing
you need to know

15:04.171 --> 15:05.605
about dealing
with disabled people --

15:05.705 --> 15:07.607
Excuse me.
Aren't we supposed to say

15:07.707 --> 15:09.642
"people with
disabilities?"

15:11.178 --> 15:12.779
You're damn right
you are!

15:12.879 --> 15:15.348
**

15:20.653 --> 15:27.660
**

15:27.760 --> 15:34.767
**

15:34.867 --> 15:41.874
**

15:42.009 --> 15:44.144
[ Shouting happily ]

15:44.244 --> 15:49.449
**

15:49.549 --> 15:51.318
Ranger: Oh!

15:54.821 --> 15:57.290
Dude. That was awesome.

15:58.391 --> 16:01.161
"Let's...go...rescue...

16:01.261 --> 16:04.164
my...dad."

16:04.264 --> 16:05.798
Ray! Think quick!

16:06.633 --> 16:08.468
Why?!

16:08.568 --> 16:09.802
Now!

16:11.504 --> 16:14.641
Brandon! You were
supposed to pull him in.

16:14.741 --> 16:16.143
I'm sorry, Dylan.

16:16.243 --> 16:17.910
It's just not
that exciting anymore.

16:18.011 --> 16:19.479
He wasn't even annoying
today.

16:19.579 --> 16:22.049
He's been kind of...cool.

16:22.149 --> 16:24.817
Thank you!
Smart is sexy!

16:24.917 --> 16:26.586
Dylan: He just
called himself sexy.

16:26.686 --> 16:30.090
Brandon. F-Fart on him.
You're scaring me.

16:30.190 --> 16:32.092
This all just
went too fast.

16:32.192 --> 16:35.595
I think...I want to
bully other people.

16:35.695 --> 16:39.532
**

16:39.632 --> 16:41.201
[ Beeping ]
JJ?!

16:41.301 --> 16:43.336
Ranger: I'm getting you
out of there!

16:43.436 --> 16:45.872
JJ? Nope.
That doesn't make any sense.

16:45.972 --> 16:47.274
Your son came
and got me.

16:47.374 --> 16:48.575
He did?

16:50.743 --> 16:53.180
You went all the way
to the ranger station?

16:53.280 --> 16:56.015
Rode through the night,
by yourself, to get help?

16:58.351 --> 16:59.619
I can't believe
you did that.

17:01.054 --> 17:03.923
Class, it's been
a long journey.

17:04.023 --> 17:07.360
We've all learned a lot,
especially me.

17:07.460 --> 17:10.430
But now, finally,
it is time for you

17:10.530 --> 17:14.634
to leave these hallowed halls
to return...

17:14.734 --> 17:18.205
to these halls...
to work.

17:18.305 --> 17:19.239
Dr. Miller: Hmm.

17:19.339 --> 17:21.241
Let's meet your students!

17:21.341 --> 17:23.710
[ Applause ]

17:23.810 --> 17:26.913
Ohh! Congratulations.
You trained them.

17:27.013 --> 17:29.382
Any chance you can
work your magic on a dog?

17:29.482 --> 17:30.617
No.

17:30.717 --> 17:32.719
Oh, look.
They're doing great.

17:32.819 --> 17:35.288
We found the right student
for each of them.

17:35.388 --> 17:37.724
This isn't the kind of book
I usually read,

17:37.824 --> 17:41.228
but we don't know each other
that well...yet.

17:43.630 --> 17:45.898
She speaks
sign language.

17:45.998 --> 17:48.235
Ohh.

17:52.105 --> 17:54.607
Oh, my God!
You're a Hufflepuff, too?!

17:54.707 --> 17:56.843
That's crazy!
We're the same person!

17:56.943 --> 17:59.412
You know, Kenneth
was right about you.

17:59.512 --> 18:01.348
What? That I'm a giant
pain in the ass?

18:01.448 --> 18:03.683
-No, he never said that.
-What did he say?

18:03.783 --> 18:04.917
He said you were tough,

18:05.017 --> 18:06.919
but you're the best mother
he'd ever met...

18:07.019 --> 18:09.956
and if these kids' moms
are like you,

18:10.056 --> 18:11.591
we'll love this job.

18:11.691 --> 18:13.993
Kenneth: Hi.

18:14.093 --> 18:15.828
And what are you two ladies
talking about?

18:15.928 --> 18:18.265
-Just your dumb face.
-Yeah, bugger off, stupid.

18:18.365 --> 18:20.700
Okay. Geez.

18:24.604 --> 18:26.506
So...

18:26.606 --> 18:28.275
About our talk earlier.

18:28.375 --> 18:31.211
[ Sighs ]
I always want to tell you

18:31.311 --> 18:34.214
that you can do anything
you set your mind to.

18:34.314 --> 18:37.450
But there are some things
you can't do.

18:37.550 --> 18:40.320
And that's okay. There are
some things I can't do.

18:40.420 --> 18:42.489
I-I can't wink
for some reason.

18:42.589 --> 18:45.158
See? It's -- It's this.

18:45.258 --> 18:50.897
I know. Your challenges are
different than...winking.

18:50.997 --> 18:53.733
And when I think
about what it would take

18:53.833 --> 18:56.803
for you to be a dad...

18:56.903 --> 18:59.138
take care of a family...

18:59.239 --> 19:01.974
it's tricky to see.

19:03.343 --> 19:06.213
But it was
also hard to imagine

19:06.313 --> 19:08.981
you going to
a mainstream school

19:09.081 --> 19:12.319
or spending a whole
summer at camp.

19:12.419 --> 19:14.821
And I certainly
could never imagine

19:14.921 --> 19:16.923
you doing
what you did today.

19:18.425 --> 19:20.760
I don't know
what the future holds,

19:20.860 --> 19:23.496
but I do know...

19:23.596 --> 19:25.398
you are extraordinary, son.

19:26.499 --> 19:28.201
And even if you don't do

19:28.301 --> 19:32.004
everything
you put your mind to,

19:32.104 --> 19:33.940
you've come
pretty damn close so far.

19:36.509 --> 19:38.611
Can you have a family?

19:38.711 --> 19:40.780
I am going to
change my answer

19:40.880 --> 19:43.015
from a patronizing...

19:43.115 --> 19:45.017
"Yeah, definitely!"...

19:45.117 --> 19:49.055
to a very sincere...

19:49.155 --> 19:50.257
"maybe."

19:52.259 --> 19:57.397
"Thank you for being H-O--
honest with me."

19:57.497 --> 19:59.899
Oh.

20:03.135 --> 20:04.804
We got to get back.

20:04.904 --> 20:06.973
We should relieve ourselves
before we hit the road.

20:08.074 --> 20:12.479
"Aren't you afraid
of the O-U-- outhouse?"

20:12.579 --> 20:16.048
Pfft! Outhouse?
We're two men in the woods!

20:16.148 --> 20:19.286
[ Urinating ]
How much did you
have to drink?

20:23.290 --> 20:25.892
**

20:25.992 --> 20:28.227
All right. Where is he?

20:28.328 --> 20:29.462
What are you doing?

20:29.562 --> 20:31.564
You and Brandon
drove me crazy.

20:31.664 --> 20:33.132
But since you parted ways,

20:33.232 --> 20:34.667
you haven't done
a single mean thing to me.

20:34.767 --> 20:36.135
I want my sister back.

20:36.235 --> 20:37.670
And if Brandon's
tired of bullying me,

20:37.770 --> 20:40.139
then I guess it's time
to spice things up.

20:40.239 --> 20:41.474
I'm a band kid now.

20:41.574 --> 20:43.410
That's really sweet, Ray.
But I don't --

20:45.645 --> 20:48.748
[ Flute playing off-key ]

20:50.983 --> 20:52.985
There he is.

20:56.155 --> 20:59.258
-Aah! Aah!
-[ Laughs ]

21:03.262 --> 21:04.831
You are bullying in front

21:04.931 --> 21:07.199
of the "no bullying" poster,
you load!

21:07.300 --> 21:09.369
You're gonna catch
your own bird this time.

21:09.469 --> 21:11.538
Mm-hmm. Gosh!

21:11.638 --> 21:14.374
I'm sorry.
It's okay.

21:14.474 --> 21:17.109
Look. Thanks for caring.
You are a good brother, Ray.

21:17.209 --> 21:20.947
And I'm sure I'll be ready to
bully you again, eventually.

21:21.047 --> 21:23.282
Can't phrase it any better than
one Sarah McLachlan, who said --

21:23.383 --> 21:24.884
Yeah, I'm ready.

21:26.786 --> 21:28.821
-Thanks, Ray!
-Good to have you back!

21:33.860 --> 21:36.863
-- Captions by VITA --
